snippet.textDisplay:
RFAK is Pakistan's pride, he is one and only. I had left a rude comment for this song until I saw Ali Noor's vlog going through comments section with his family and I realized that just disapproving something without providing any reason is not a just thing to do. I honestly felt very bad when Ali read that Zina comment. 

My impression of the song persists, it doesn't live up to the original and reason that I understand is that you guys started really well, Ali Noor was really good, I'm sure this song would have sounded a lot better if only Ali Noor had sung it alone. RFAK doesn't have that kind of voice to sing a song like Sayonee. I liked the slow starting part. Tempo changed quickly and I was like Ron Burgundy "that escalated quickly", and then comes the moment when you are expecting a masculine voice for the word sayonee and comes RFAK with his sweet cute slightly feminine voice which feels like he is making fun of the original song. I'm a huge fan of Noori's aik alif from coke studio, if Ali Noor reads my comment and I hope that he does, I just want to say that you did nothing wrong, in fact your part was the only good part, i won't say not to get dishearted because I'm sure you are tough enough to take minor blows, we Pakistanis don't usually care much about other's feelings when it comes to commenting. Salman bhai again is probably one of the best guitarist and sayonee's tune is famous all over, I respect him a lot and admire his PTI support too. In this song, he overdid the solo part.

I watched coke studio from season 1 to see what has changed and what I have realized is that we are not seeing classical ustaads with diverse artists anymore, Rohail's music is simple but polished. Strings is doing experiments and Rohail did too, as long as Strings doesn't shake the ideology (which it looks like shaking) behind Coke studio project, they are talented and they can turn in good music. 

Good opening by Ali Noor, sudden disappointment from RFAK, overdone solo in the ending. Score 3/5.
